body_html:
for FetchOutputs issue
I think you must quantize you pb file with --output_node_names="output"
like this:
bazel-bin/tensorflow/contrib/quantization/tools/quantize_graph --input=tensorflow_inception_graph.pb --output_node_names="output" --print_nodes=true --output=tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/camera/data/quantized_tensorflow_inception_graph.pb --mode=eightbit --logtostderr

Hi @petewarden
I run the quantized-pb on camera example of ios
It's well, but I get info:

Zero is not representable in the quantized range used by the input. This means QuantizedConv2d has to fall back to a slow implementation, since the border of zero values can't be represented easily. You should try to construct graphs that avoid this situation.

How to avoid this info?
